The adult male specimens examined were collected together with those of three other species described in the present paper. For details on ecology and bionomics see notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D5DFFCFFFA4FAECF8D2EA6CAF98" authorityName="Dantas &amp; Amat &amp; Hamada &amp; Giłka" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiensis">
<emphasis id="B979EACCFFCFFFA4FAECF8D2EA6CAF98" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="511">Tanytarsus colombiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
